definition.value: Cell type found in both hemibrain and FAFB (Schlegel et al., 2021).

label.value: adult lateral horn-fan-shaped body layer 2 neuron

value.value: Adult lateral horn output neuron that has wide-field (tangential) presynaptic arborization in fan-shaped body layer 2 (Dolan et al., 2019; Hulse et al., 2021). There are four of these neurons per hemisphere and they are glutamatergic (Dolan et al., 2019) and they develop from the CP2 neuroblast (Kandimalla et al., 2023).

definition.value: Hulse et al. (2021) say LHPV5k1 likely corresponds to FB2H_a, FB2H_b and/or FB2I_b, as does Schlegel et al. (2021) supplement. Schlegel et al. (2021) map this type to a different tract than other PV5 neurons, so PV5k1 name is misleading and this neuron is not part of the DL2 dorsal or DL1 dorsal hemilineage. All FB2I and FB2H mapped to CP2 lineage in Kandimalla et al. (2023). Dolan et al. (2019) say this is glutamatergic (based on immunohistochemistry), but Schlegel et al. (2021) predict cholinergic based on lineage.

There are around 14 of these neurons per hemisphere and they are cholinergic (Dolan et al., 2019; Schlegel et al., 2021).

value.value: Adult lateral horn output neuron that fasciculates with the PV6 primary neurite tract (Dolan et al., 2019). There are five of these neurons per hemisphere and they are cholinergic (Dolan et al., 2019).

label.value: adult lateral horn PV10c1 neuron

value.value: Adult lateral horn output neuron that fasciculates with the PV10 primary neurite tract (Frechter et al., 2019). It is a secondary neuron that develops from the DM1 (DPMm1) neuroblast (Bates et al., 2020). It has predominantly dendritic arborization in the ipsilateral mushroom body calyx, lateral horn and superior lateral protocerebrum (Marin et al., 2020). It also descends to the subesophageal zone, where it arborizes in both hemispheres (Marin et al., 2020). There is around one of these cells per hemisphere (Schlegel et al., 2021).

label.value: adult lateral horn PV12a1 neuron

value.value: Adult lateral horn neuron that fasciculates with the PV12 primary neurite tract (Dolan et al., 2019; Schlegel et al., 2021). It is a primary neuron (Bates et al., 2020). There is approximately one of these neurons per hemisphere and it is GABAergic (Dolan et al., 2019; Bates et al., 2020). It innervates both mushroom body calyces and lateral horns is synapsed to and by a wide range of projection neuron axons (Bates et al., 2020).

definition.value: Dolan et al. (2019) class as input neuron, Schlegel et al. (2021) class as output neuron.

label.value: adult AVLP-PN1 lateral horn input neuron

value.value: Adult lateral horn input neuron that has its dendrites predominantly within the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (Dolan et al., 2019; Baker et al., 2022). There are ten of these neurons per hemisphere and they are cholinergic and GABAergic (Dolan et al., 2019). It responds to both male sine and pulse song (Baker et al., 2022).
